1
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:59,080
Do you believe it, Zuliang?

2
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:15,560
Madam.

3
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:20,010
Today's newspaper.

4
00:02:20,480 --> 00:02:21,320
Thank you.

5
00:02:21,720 --> 00:02:23,520
Are the master's books all packed up?

6
00:02:23,520 --> 00:02:25,480
The master's books filled several boxes.

7
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:26,940
And the car has been hired.

8
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:30,360
I can't take these boxes with me either.

9
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:32,240
Please help move them to the countryside.

10
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:33,280
Yes, Madam.

11
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:40,680
Wanfu.

12
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:41,600
Wanfu.

13
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:42,240
Madam.

14
00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:42,920
Look.

15
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:43,840
What is it?

16
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,400
Your brigade commander.

17
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:49,820
Is it your brigade commander?

18
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:57,160
Look at these shoulders.

19
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:58,200
This silhouette,

20
00:03:58,520 --> 00:03:59,840
this is Yunkui.

21
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:02,800
No, Madam,

22
00:04:03,320 --> 00:04:05,050
it's too blurry to see clearly.

23
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:07,930
Then go into the light and take a good look.

24
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,360
Is it him?

25
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:11,120
It must be him.

26
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:15,040
I've always had a feeling.

27
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:16,920
I feel that Yunkui is not dead.

28
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:17,680
These past two days,

29
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:18,560
a voice kept telling me

30
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:19,820
Yunkui is still alive.

31
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:23,960
No, Madam,

32
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:25,400
this is too blurry.

33
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:27,200
How could anyone recognize him?

34
00:04:33,159 --> 00:04:33,760
Come here.

35
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:34,560
Madam.

36
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:37,480
Twenty-one, twenty-two,

37
00:04:37,480 --> 00:04:39,120
twenty-three, twenty-four,

38
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:39,680
twenty-five...

39
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:40,200
Madam.

40
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:41,400
Don't speak.

41
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:42,920
Twenty-six, twenty-seven,

42
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,240
twenty-eight, twenty-nine...

43
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:44,920
Madam.

44
00:04:45,880 --> 00:04:46,400
Madam!

45
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:47,880
I told you not to speak.

46
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:49,520
Just help me count.

47
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:51,400
Help you count what?

48
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:52,240
Where was I?

49
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:53,200
What do you mean?

50
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:54,320
What number was I on?

51
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:55,400
No, what are you talking about?

52
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:57,460
You have to tell me what you're doing.

53
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:01,880
Yunkui,

54
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:04,610
he liked the broad beans I made for him.

55
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:05,800
Every time he went out,

56
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,200
I would pack a bag for him.

57
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:10,280
He forgot to take them when he left that day.

58
00:05:10,280 --> 00:05:12,200
So I chased after him with the broad beans.

59
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,880
I couldn't find him along the way.

60
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:15,680
I thought I was going to lose him.

61
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:16,600
Right there,

62
00:05:16,640 --> 00:05:18,200
I ran into him right there.

63
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,280
If I walk from here

64
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:21,560
back home,

65
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,760
and the number of steps is even,

66
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:25,760
he is still alive.

67
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:28,520
No.

68
00:05:28,880 --> 00:05:29,880
No.

69
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:31,440
No.

70
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:40,120
One, two, three, four,

71
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:43,240
five, six, seven, eight,

72
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:45,560
nine, ten, eleven, twelve,

73
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:48,200
thirteen, fourteen, fifteen, sixteen,

74
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:51,240
seventeen, eighteen, nineteen, twenty.

75
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:53,720
1,567.

76
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:55,440
1,568.

77
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:57,040
1,569.

78
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:58,560
1,570.

79
00:05:59,080 --> 00:06:00,480
1,571.

80
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:01,760
1,572.

81
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:03,000
1,573.

82
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,320
1,574.

83
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:05,680
1,575.

84
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,160
1,576.

85
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:08,600
1,577.

86
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:09,840
1,578.

87
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:11,080
1,579.

88
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:13,880
1,580.

89
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:15,600
An even number.

90
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:23,250
This is where Yunkui left that day,

91
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:26,240
when he kowtowed to his father for the last time.

92
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:27,370
It's an even number.

93
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:28,640
He's still alive.

94
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:30,880
Ma'am, what does this have to do with anything?

95
00:06:30,880 --> 00:06:32,280
This is too childish.

96
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:34,930
My wishes with even numbers always come true.

97
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:36,760
Do you know how many broad beans

98
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:37,920
I packed for Yunkui?

99
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:38,920
Ma'am.

100
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:40,240
622.

101
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:41,680
Do you know why

102
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:42,800
it was 622?

103
00:06:43,520 --> 00:06:44,440
Because

104
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:46,640
the day I met him

105
00:06:47,159 --> 00:06:48,680
was June 22nd.

106
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:50,800
It...

107
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:52,520
Does this have anything to do with

108
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:54,360
our brigade commander still being alive?

109
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:55,880
The day Yunkui died,

110
00:06:56,840 --> 00:06:58,159
did you see it clearly?

111
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:00,880
I saw it clearly.

112
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,520
What did you see clearly?

113
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:05,960
I saw clearly that the position was gone.

114
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:07,280
Was the position gone,

115
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,960
or were the people gone?

116
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:11,720
Ma'am.

117
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:13,960
The position was gone,

118
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:16,120
and the people were gone too.

119
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:17,780
All 6,000 brothers were gone.

120
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:19,760
I want to see him alive or dead.

121
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:20,680
So,

122
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,880
you didn't see him, right?

123
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:28,160
Wanfu.

124
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:31,210
You haven't been with him for long,

125
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:33,440
so you didn't see clearly.

126
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:35,280
I don't blame you.

127
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:37,960
Father.

128
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:38,560
Madam.

129
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:39,120
Father.

130
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:39,960
Madam.

131
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:40,720
Father.

132
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:42,480
Yujiao.

133
00:07:42,520 --> 00:07:42,840
Father.

134
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:44,040
Everything is ready.

135
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,400
Yunkui is still alive.

136
00:07:50,440 --> 00:07:52,040
Look at the photo.

137
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:58,640
Right here.

138
00:07:58,760 --> 00:08:00,160
This is Yunkui.

139
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:03,480
This is a photo of the Scouts visiting

140
00:08:03,480 --> 00:08:04,960
the Shanghai field hospital.

141
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:06,440
Yunkui must have been injured

142
00:08:06,440 --> 00:08:07,680
and sent to the hospital,

143
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:09,720
so he happened to be photographed.

144
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:11,080
Wanfu also said

145
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:13,160
he didn't see Yunkui die with his own eyes.

146
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:13,880
No, Master.

147
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:15,200
I didn't say that.

148
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:16,520
You did.

149
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:18,200
I said the brigade commander and the position

150
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:19,040
are both gone.

151
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:21,660
Dad, the hospital is in Shanghai.

152
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,720
Let's go to Shanghai to find Yunkui.

153
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:25,160
What? Go to Shanghai?

154
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:26,280
I'm telling you, Master,

155
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:27,640
you can't listen to Madam.

156
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:29,040
Shanghai is a war zone now.

157
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,240
The army could withdraw at any time.

158
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:31,040
After they withdraw, it'll be

159
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:31,920
the Japanese territory.

160
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:32,840
How dangerous is that!

161
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:33,400
Look,

162
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:35,120
Madam is still pregnant.

163
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,640
But Yunkui is in Shanghai.

164
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:37,700
We have to find him.

165
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,880
Madam, you just said it yourself.

166
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:40,140
It's a field hospital.

167
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:41,080
By the time you get to Shanghai,

168
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:42,600
the hospital might not even be there.

169
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:43,840
Even if the hospital is gone,

170
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:45,840
the reporter who wrote this article is still there.

171
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:46,800
As long as we find the newspaper office

172
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:47,480
and the reporter,

173
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:48,680
we can find Yunkui.

174
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:49,640
No, Master.

175
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:51,000
Madam is completely crazy now.

176
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,360
Do you know what she just did?

177
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:53,680
She took me to the bridge

178
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:54,680
and paced back.

179
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:56,280
She said if it's an even number, the brigade commander is alive.

180
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,520
If it's an odd number, he's dead.

181
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:58,640
Isn't this a joke?

182
00:08:58,640 --> 00:08:59,720
That has nothing to do with this.

183
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:01,080
She insisted she walked

184
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:02,080
1,580 steps.

185
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:03,720
Then I said I walked

186
00:09:03,880 --> 00:09:04,880
1,581 steps.

187
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:05,960
Shut up!

188
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,640
You can't see clearly.

189
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:12,720
I can see clearly.

190
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:20,640
Yujiao,

191
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:23,040
to be honest,

192
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,600
my eyes are dim,

193
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,800
I can't see clearly either.

194
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,560
Is this Yunkui?

195
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:31,320
Dad, look.

196
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:33,400
'National Salvation Times.'

197
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:34,660
This is today's paper.

198
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:35,760
Front page.

199
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,800
Time, location,

200
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:39,360
and Yunkui's war zone.

201
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:40,440
They all match.

202
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:41,400
And

203
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:43,960
I'm the only one who has seen Yunkui

204
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:44,840
looking silly outside the window

205
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:46,480
after waking up in the morning.

206
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:48,360
I know I have no way to prove it.

207
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:50,640
I don't know how to explain it either.

208
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:52,640
But this is Yunkui.

209
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:53,720
Dad,

210
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:56,340
can you recognize him?

211
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,320
Child,

212
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:02,480
let me ask you,

213
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:04,720
tell me the truth.

214
00:10:05,920 --> 00:10:08,880
Do you believe the one you saw

215
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:10,920
is Yunkui?

216
00:10:14,760 --> 00:10:16,080
It must be him.

217
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:17,160
Okay.

218
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:19,560
I believe you.

219
00:10:20,880 --> 00:10:22,560
This is Yunkui.

220
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:25,920
Yunkui is still alive.

221
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:29,560
Dad,

222
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:32,240
I want to go to Shanghai to find Yunkui.

223
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:36,400
What Wanfu just said is right.

224
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:38,440
Shanghai is not safe now.

225
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:39,840
So you and Sister Liu

226
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:41,240
should go to Wuhan.

227
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:43,580
Aren't you going to Wuhan?

228
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:44,760
Here's an extra ticket.

229
00:10:44,760 --> 00:10:45,680
Take it.

230
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:48,440
No, I'm going with you.

231
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:51,100
We can't be separated at a time like this.

232
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:51,800
Dad!

233
00:10:51,920 --> 00:10:53,280
I promised Yunkui

234
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:55,720
that we would never be separated.

235
00:10:57,840 --> 00:10:58,600
Wanfu.

236
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:00,680
Ayi said he's quitting

237
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,440
and going back to his hometown.

238
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:04,280
Good, let him take these large items

239
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:05,920
back for us.

240
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:08,600
Wanfu.

241
00:11:09,120 --> 00:11:11,520
Where are the three tickets to Wuhan?

242
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,280
Keep one for yourself.

243
00:11:13,680 --> 00:11:15,240
Sell the other two

244
00:11:15,560 --> 00:11:16,840
for travel expenses.

245
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:19,080
Consider it a token of gratitude

246
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:21,040
from the Zhang family.

247
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:23,440
No, this... Master...

248
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:25,840
Yujiao.

249
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:27,000
I know

250
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:28,920
if I don't let you go to Shanghai,

251
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:30,960
you'll never have peace of mind.

252
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:33,320
Come, let's pack and go to Shanghai.

253
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:34,880
Let's go.

254
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:37,640
Yunkui is still alive.

255
00:11:38,920 --> 00:11:40,960
Crazy. Everyone's crazy.

256
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:43,440
This family acts on every whim.

257
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:05,080
Whatever you plan to do next,

258
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:07,120
you must heal your wounds first.

259
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:09,080
Fortunately,

260
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:10,680
no one knows who you are here.

261
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:12,480
You are now No. 157,

262
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:13,360
Officer Li.

263
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:16,120
Our hospital has received orders

264
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:18,000
to retreat along the Wufu Line

265
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,160
to Nanjing

266
00:12:19,240 --> 00:12:20,480
and prepare to defend the national defense line.

267
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:22,920
Tonight, all equipment and personnel

268
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:23,920
will be transferred.

269
00:12:23,920 --> 00:12:25,840
When does the first batch retreat?

270
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:28,240
The severely wounded leave first tonight.

271
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:30,840
Liao Fengnian and Sun Huaiyi

272
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:33,560
should have already retreated to Nanjing.

273
00:12:33,560 --> 00:12:34,160
Arrange for me to leave tonight

274
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:36,360
with these severely wounded soldiers.

275
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:39,440
You absolutely cannot appear in Nanjing.

276
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:40,520
If someone recognizes you,

277
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:42,380
you'll be arrested immediately.

278
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:47,320
My 6,000 brothers died for the country.

279
00:12:47,520 --> 00:12:49,240
I can't let them bear the infamy of a deserter

280
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:50,360
like me.

281
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:51,920
They won't rest in peace.

282
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:00,970
Brother Yunkui.

283
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:03,080
You haven't fully recovered yet.

284
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:06,360
Besides, the frontal battlefield is a mess right now.

285
00:13:06,640 --> 00:13:09,440
Shanghai and Taiyuan are both in imminent danger.

286
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:12,160
Professor Shen, my university mentor, also mentioned

287
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:14,090
that his friend Xie Yufeng's side,

288
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:16,200
the Communist troops, have already gone deep behind enemy lines.

289
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:19,240
This new force cannot be underestimated.

290
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:20,650
Brother Yunkui.

291
00:13:20,720 --> 00:13:21,980
The world is changing.

292
